<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/766825-are-the-father-brown-books-appropriate-for">Are the Father Brown books appropriate for children? My 10 yo has a voracious appetite, and loves mysteries. Thanks!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_766825'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F671140.The_Complete_Father_Brown_Stories">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/766825-are-the-father-brown-books-appropriate-for">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/766825-are-the-father-brown-books-appropriate-for">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/43039871-joe-mcmahon"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1431545273i/43039871._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/43039871-joe-mcmahon">Joe McMahon</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Most of them are OK, as Ravinder notes, there are a number of racist references, most to people of color, but also to religions and non-English people<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Most of them are OK, as Ravinder notes, there are a number of racist references, most to people of color, but also to religions and non-English people. Chesterton does tend to use stereotypes in places that he could written more fully-delineated characters, and is frankly not very good at all with non-Christian religions. I too would recommend pre-reading, or reading with, and discussing the unfortunate choices.<br /><br />I read them in middle-school myself, at about 13-14, so they're not *inappropriate*, just not 100% in line with current standards.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link738674" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=738674&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F766825-are-the-father-brown-books-appropriate-for%2Fanswers%2F738674-most-of-them-are-ok">flag</a>
</div>
